Twitter is trying to make it more interesting for new users
Twitter’s microblogging service has changed the process of registering users to engage new members more quickly in active interaction with the platform.
This measure should reduce the number of people who have left their microblogs.
Now, new Twitter users will be browsing through a large number of service-recommended accounts during registration to immediately form their reading circle.
