The creator of Coming Out Simulator will release a game about modern journalism
Game designer Nikki Case, known for the game Coming Out Simulator, decided to release a game about modern journalism.
He told about his project in an interview with Kill Screen.
Case started working on the game a few weeks ago, but this fact has only gained widespread notoriety now.
The inspiration for the game was the events in Ferguson, where protests are now taking place, which began after a policeman killed an unarmed black teenager.
The focus of the project, which does not yet have a title, will be how informational coverage of stories affects their consequences.
The hero of the game, a civilian journalist, will need to photograph what is happening in areas where clashes between the police and the population take place.
The hero can take different pictures of what is happening, which will affect the course of events.
If he shoots the scene in such a way that the police will look like heroes, and the protesters will look like bandits, the police will start treating him better and letting him where the ordinary person can not go.
If he illuminates events differently, his photographs could turn peaceful protests into large-scale riots.
Points in the game will need to be scored with the help of the hero's twitter, in which new subscribers will appear, if the photos displayed there will be popular.
The game has no name yet.
The date of release and the platform on which it will appear is unknown.
Case, however, published an image demonstrating how the event could change depending on how the photo about it was taken and processed.
In an interview with Kill Screen Case explained that he had been thinking about the concept of such a game for a long time, but initially wanted to dedicate it not to protests in the United States, but to events in the Gaza Strip.
After he started collecting material for the game, the game designer realized that he lacked the knowledge and skills to shed light on the history of the region.
However, when he saw the media covering the events in Ferguson, he decided to make the game based on what happened.
Nikki Case is an independent developer who produces browser-based games.
His most famous project was Coming Out Simulator, released in 2014.
This game, which tells about the events from the biography of Case himself, is dedicated to how a bisexual teenager tries to tell about his relationship with homophobic parents.
