Less than half of all books are purchased in university bookstores, according to the professional association "National Association of University Stores".
Here is an introductory course on the best ways to make a profitable deal.
Purchase in the online store
Sometimes, if you go online, the price of a new book can be one-third of what you’ll see in a university bookstore.
The ninth edition of The Mathematical Analysis of Ron Larson, Bruce Edwards, and Robert Hostetler costs about $290 per price tag, but a new copy can be purchased for $239.99 at Chegg.com, which specializes in textbook sales.
Purchase of used
If you are not against other people’s marks or injuries, used textbooks are a good option.
"Mathematical Analysis" is sold for $93.49 as used on Chegg.com.
Matt Cassadey, 25, a fourth-year student at Brigham Young University, says he paid Amazon.com 42 cents for a copy of the book “Strategic Solutions in Media: Understanding the Business Side of Advertising.”
The book sold for $48.
Teachers, for example, Ingrid Bracy, director of the College Without Walls at the University of Massachusetts at Emherst, offers students to clarify with their professors whether they can use previous editions.
Updates are sometimes not necessary for classes.
In such cases, old editions can often be found for a very small fraction of the cost of the last edition.
In addition to the Chegg and Amazon sites, Half.com, owned by eBay Inc., is a popular alternative to buying used books.
Rent-a-car
About taking the textbooks for rent, it is worth thinking, if you treat them well enough, do not forget to return them and do not want to leave them to yourself after the course is over.
You can save more than 80% of the cost of a new book.
For example, one student was able to rent Mathematical Analysis for a semester for about $20.
