"Europrotocol" instead of reference to the BIBDD
Cash payments can be obtained without a certificate from the BIBDD – so the Central Bank intends to stimulate the implementation of the “Europrotocol” in Russia.
The Bank of Russia has developed a draft of guidelines according to which from September 1 this year, an insured motorist will be able to do without a certificate of BIBDD to receive cash payments.
The issue, however, is only those cases where the accident was registered under the “Europrotocol” without the participation of the road police.
That is, if only two cars were involved in the accident, there are no physically injured persons, the damage does not exceed the set limit and both drivers have reached an agreement on who is responsible for the accident.
From August 2, the limit of payments under the "Europrotocol" is 50 thousand rubles, and from October 1, in Moscow, St. Petersburg, as well as in the Moscow and Leningrad regions, it will be increased to 400 thousand rubles.
The bottom line is that often, even in minor injuries, in a situation where an accident can be registered under the “Europrotocol”, drivers who are in an accident cause an accident.
After all, if there is a policy helmet to get a refund on it without a certificate of the BIBDD was not possible.
The parameters prescribed in the draft directive are precisely designed to eliminate this obstacle on the way to the implementation of the “Europrotocol” in Russia.
According to them, the maximum cash payment in connection with the accident, issued without the staff of the BIDD, should not be lower than the limit under the "Europrotocol".
But at the same time, it can not be above the limit set in the insurance contract Casco.
The idea is certainly useful and theoretically able to unload both DPS employees and the road.
